data.description: Under Contract with 72 Hour Kick out Clause in place. Accepting Back up offers. A beautiful all brick 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom 1790 ft. home located close to Hurlburt Field and just minutes to our famous sugar white sand beaches. This home was built in 2012 by one of the prominent builders in the area, Watree Homes. Besides building a quality home, some of the great things I like about this builder is they included the ManaBlock plumbing system, a kitchen with designer cabinetry and soft-close doors and drawers, nice-sized pantry, 20'' porcelain tile in the wet areas, tumbled stone back splash in the kitchen, GE Stainless Steel appliances and granite counter tops. The homes layout if perfect, with an open concept kitchen and living areas and split bedroom floor plan. In 2017 the home was upgraded with new luxury vinyl plank flooring in the master bedroom, living room, foyer and hallway. The large master bedroom features a beautiful trey ceiling, large walk in closet and the master bath has a double vanity a walk in shower and an over-sized garden tub. High Efficiency Low-E vinyl Windows with custom blinds, Quiet Zone insulation for the Master Bedroom that separates sound from the main living area. On top of all those amazing features is one that's a huge plus and really makes this home stand out, the owners recently added a $35k+ very spacious and well-built Florida room to the back of the home, perfect place to enjoy summer days without bugs, cool evenings and room for entertaining. Did I mention the newly sodded front and back yard is has plenty of room for a pool, playground area, storage building or all of the above. The spacious garage is trimmed and finished and includes a quiet belt driven garage door opener. The exterior of the home includes hurricane protection with exterior hardware pre-installed for all windows and doors and high efficiency low-E vinyl Windows. This home has tons of features that make it a quality home ready for it's new owners. Make your appointments to see this home soon. Measurements and information are believed to be accurate, buyer should verify all information deemed important.
